OL,7,FHe said: "It's either going to be the
OL,8,FGovernment, in which case they need to
OL,9,Fput taxes up, or it's going to be paid
OL,10,Ffor by other energy customers, in
OL,11,Fwhich case bills go up for everyone
OL,12,Fwho's not getting it. The challenge is
OL,13,Fthat bills are already too high."
OL,15,FInstead, the Octopus boss has been
OL,16,Flobbying ministers to introduce
OL,17,Fanother pricing system, based on
OL,18,Fproximity to where clean energy is
OL,19,Fgenerated, to reform bills.
